        opts: ["Very small breasts", "Abnormal mammograms, dense breast tissue, post-operative scar tissue, or breast implants", "Only early-stage cancers", "Calcifications larger than 5 cm"],
        ans: 1
      },
      {
        q: "Scintimammography has higher sensitivity than conventional mammography but is less accurate for abnormalities smaller than:",
        opts: ["0.5 cm", "1 cm", "2 cm", "3 cm"],
        ans: 1
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    lecture: 14,
    title: "Fluoroscopy",
    questions: [
      {
        q: "Fluoroscopy differs from conventional radiography in that it provides:",
        opts: ["Static images of internal structures", "Real-time moving images of internal structures", "Three-dimensional reconstructions of organs", "Images using radioactive tracers"],
        ans: 1
      },
      {
        q: "Which of the following is a common clinical application of fluoroscopy?",
        opts: ["Measuring bone mineral density", "Angiography of the leg, heart, and cerebral vessels", "Early detection of breast cancer", "Measuring lung volume"],
        ans: 1
      },
      {
        q: "A C-arm fluoroscopic unit is most commonly used in:",
        opts: ["Breast imaging departments", "Operating rooms for orthopedic procedures", "Dedicated barium study rooms only", "Nuclear medicine departments"],
        ans: 1
      },
      {
        q: "The image intensifier tube is approximately how long and operates in what condition?",
        opts: ["10 cm long, in a pressurized environment", "50 cm long, in a vacuum", "30 cm long, filled with nitrogen gas", "20 cm long, in a saline solution"],
        ans: 1
      },
      {
        q: "The input phosphor of the image intensifier is made of cesium iodide and serves to:",
        opts: ["Convert electrons into visible light at the output", "Convert incident X-ray photons into a burst of visible light photons", "Accelerate photoelectrons toward the anode", "Focus the electron beam using electrostatic lenses"],
        ans: 1
      },
      {
        q: "The photocathode of the image intensifier converts light photons into electrons by the process of:",
        opts: ["Thermionic emission", "Photoemission", "Compton scatter", "Pair production"],
        ans: 1
      },
      {
        q: "A potential difference of approximately how much accelerates electrons toward the anode in the image intensifier?",
        opts: ["1,000 V", "5,000 V", "25,000 V", "100,000 V"],
        ans: 2
      },
      {
        q: "The output phosphor of the image intensifier converts photoelectrons to light photons, multiplying each incident photoelectron into:",
        opts: ["2-5 light photons", "10-20 light photons", "50-75 light photons", "100-200 light photons"],
        ans: 2
      },
      {
        q: "Brightness Gain of the image intensifier is calculated as:",
        opts: ["Magnification gain + Flux gain", "Magnification gain x Flux gain", "Flux gain / Magnification gain", "Magnification gain - Flux gain"],
        ans: 1
      },
      {
        q: "Magnification gain in the image intensifier is the ratio of:",
        opts: ["Output phosphor diameter squared to input phosphor diameter squared", "The square of the diameter of the input phosphor to the square of the diameter of the output phosphor", "Number of output photons to number of input photons", "Input phosphor diameter to output phosphor diameter"],
        ans: 1
      },
      {
        q: "In Digital Subtraction Angiography (DSA), a mask image is acquired before contrast administration. The purpose of the mask is to:",
        opts: ["Enhance the bone structures in the image", "Be subtracted from subsequent images to remove distracting structures such as bones", "Increase the radiation dose for better contrast", "Set the correct kVp automatically"],
        ans: 1
      },
      {
        q: "Image subtraction in DSA causes a decrease in signal-to-noise ratio, making images noisier. The solution is to:",
        opts: ["Decrease kVp", "Increase mA", "Decrease the frame rate", "Increase the SID"],
        ans: 1
      },
      {
        q: "Pulsed fluoroscopy with a variety of frame rates is used in modern angiography units primarily for:",
        opts: ["Increasing image resolution", "Dose reduction", "Eliminating the need for contrast agents", "Increasing image magnification"],
        ans: 1
      },
      {
        q: "The modern angiography unit image matrix is at least:",
        opts: ["256 x 256 pixels", "512 x 512 pixels", "1024 x 1024 pixels", "2048 x 2048 pixels"],
        ans: 2
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    lecture: 15,
    title: "Bone Density Scan (DEXA) & OPG",
    questions: [
      {
        q: "DEXA (Dual-energy X-ray Absorptiometry) is the most standard method for diagnosing:",
        opts: ["Breast cancer", "Osteoporosis and assessing fracture risk", "Lung nodules", "Dental caries"],
        ans: 1
      },
      {
        q: "In DXA scanning, the X-ray source is located:",
        opts: ["Over the patient's body", "Under the examination table, moving with the detection system", "At the patient's side", "Fixed above the gantry"],
        ans: 1
      },
      {
        q: "DXA uses an X-ray beam composed of two different photon energies. The purpose of using two energies is to:",
        opts: ["Increase image resolution", "Compensate for the different attenuation coefficients of mineralized bone and soft tissues", "Reduce patient dose by half", "Eliminate the need for positioning the patient"],
        ans: 1
      },
      {
        q: "In DXA analysis, the attenuation values of soft tissues are subtracted by an algorithm, providing only:",
        opts: ["Attenuation values of fat tissue", "Attenuation values of bone", "Attenuation values of muscle tissue", "Combined attenuation of all tissues"],
        ans: 1
      },
      {
        q: "The bone attenuation values obtained in DXA are compared with standard values in phantoms to obtain:",
        opts: ["Bone volume in cubic centimeters", "Bone mineral content in grams", "Bone density in Hounsfield units", "Bone thickness in millimeters"],
        ans: 1
      },
      {
        q: "DXA can also estimate body composition because fat, bone mineral, and fat-free soft tissue have:",
        opts: ["The same absorption properties", "Different absorption properties", "Identical HVL values", "The same linear attenuation coefficients"],
        ans: 1
      },
      {
        q: "A major consideration limiting large-scale population screening with DXA is that:",
        opts: ["DXA produces very high radiation doses", "Although small, radiation dose still interferes with feasibility for large-scale screenings", "DXA requires general anesthesia", "DXA machines are not portable"],
        ans: 1
      },
      {
        q: "OPG (Orthopantomogram) is also known as panoramic radiography and captures:",
        opts: ["A single tooth in high detail", "All teeth and jaws in a single image", "A cross-sectional slice of the jaw", "The temporomandibular joint only"],
        ans: 1
      },
      {
        q: "The X-ray source in the OPG machine emits what type of beam?",
        opts: ["A wide cone beam covering the entire face at once", "A narrow fan-shaped beam that sweeps across the patient's face", "A pencil beam scanning point by point", "A parallel beam perpendicular to the jaw"],
        ans: 1
      },
      {
        q: "Patient positioning in OPG requires that the mid-sagittal plane is:",
        opts: ["Parallel to the floor", "Perpendicular to the floor", "Tilted at 15 degrees", "Aligned with the X-ray beam direction"],
        ans: 1
      },
      {
        q: "The OPG machine performs a rotational sweep lasting approximately:",
        opts: ["2-5 seconds", "10-20 seconds", "30-60 seconds", "2-3 minutes"],
        ans: 1
      },
      {
        q: "Which of the following is an advantage of OPG as an extra-oral radiograph?",
        opts: ["It provides cross-sectional 3D images", "There are fewer limitations when the patient has difficulty opening their mouth or has a prominent gag reflex", "It uses no ionizing radiation", "It has higher resolution than intraoral X-rays for individual teeth"],
        ans: 1
      },
      {
        q: "CBCT (Cone Beam Computed Tomography) provides what advantage over OPG?",
        opts: ["Lower radiation dose than OPG", "Three-dimensional imaging with a 1:1 ratio with anatomical structures, overcoming limitations of 2D OPG", "Faster acquisition time than OPG", "No need for patient positioning"],
        ans: 1
      },
      {
        q: "Despite CBCT's advantages, panoramic OPG imaging remains relevant because:",
        opts: ["OPG produces better image quality than CBCT for all purposes", "CBCT is more expensive and involves higher radiation doses, making OPG still preferred for initial screenings", "OPG provides 3D images at lower cost", "CBCT cannot image the temporomandibular joint"],
        ans: 1
      }
    ]
  }
];

// ===== STATE =====
let currentLecture = null;
let currentQuestions = [];
let currentIndex = 0;
let score = 0;
let answered = false;
let translatedQ = false;
let translatedOpts = false;

// ===== INIT =====
function init() {
  const list = document.getElementById('lectures-list');
  list.innerHTML = '';
  QUESTIONS_DATA.forEach((lec, i) => {
    const card = document.createElement('div');
    card.className = 'lec-card glass';
    card.style.animationDelay = (i * 0.05) + 's';
    card.innerHTML = `
      <div class="lec-num">L${lec.lecture.toString().padStart(2,'0')}</div>
      <div class="lec-body">
        <div class="lec-name">${lec.title}</div>
        <div class="lec-count">${lec.questions.length} سؤال</div>
      </div>
      <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--blue)" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="9 18 15 12 9 6"/></svg>
    `;
    card.onclick = () => startLecture(i);
    list.appendChild(card);
  });
}

function startLecture(idx) {
  currentLecture = QUESTIONS_DATA[idx];
  currentQuestions = [...currentLecture.questions];
  currentIndex = 0;
  score = 0;
  showScreen('screen-quiz');
  document.getElementById('prog-lec-name').textContent = currentLecture.title;
  renderQuestion();
}

function renderQuestion() {
  answered = false;
  translatedQ = false;
  translatedOpts = false;
  const q = currentQuestions[currentIndex];
  const total = currentQuestions.length;

  document.getElementById('prog-count').textContent = `${currentIndex + 1}/${total}`;
  document.getElementById('prog-fill').style.width = ((currentIndex + 1) / total * 100) + '%';
  document.getElementById('q-text').textContent = q.q;
  document.getElementById('next-btn').style.display = 'none';

  const wrap = document.getElementById('opts-wrap');
  wrap.innerHTML = '';
  const letters = ['A','B','C','D'];
  q.opts.forEach((opt, i) => {
    const div = document.createElement('div');
    div.className = 'opt glass';
    div.style.animationDelay = (i * 0.07) + 's';
    div.innerHTML = `<div class="opt-letter">${letters[i]}</div><span>${opt}</span>`;
    div.onclick = () => selectAnswer(i, div, q.ans);
    wrap.appendChild(div);
  });
}

function selectAnswer(chosen, el, correct) {
  if (answered) return;
  answered = true;
  const opts = document.querySelectorAll('#opts-wrap .opt');
  opts.forEach((o, i) => {
    o.style.pointerEvents = 'none';
    if (i === correct) o.classList.add('correct');
    else if (i === chosen && chosen !== correct) o.classList.add('wrong');
  });
  if (chosen === correct) score++;
  document.getElementById('next-btn').style.display = 'block';
}

function nextQuestion() {
  currentIndex++;
  if (currentIndex >= currentQuestions.length) {
    showResult();
  } else {
    renderQuestion();
  }
}

function showResult() {
  showScreen('screen-result');
  document.getElementById('result-score').textContent = `${score}/${currentQuestions.length}`;
}

function goHome() {
  showScreen('screen-home');
}

function showScreen(id) {
  document.querySelectorAll('.screen').forEach(s => s.classList.remove('active'));
  document.getElementById(id).classList.add('active');
  window.scrollTo(0, 0);
}

function translateQuestion() {
  const el = document.getElementById('q-text');
  const q = currentQuestions[currentIndex];
  if (!translatedQ) {
    const ar = translateToArabic(q.q);
    el.innerHTML = `<span style="display:block;">${q.q}</span><span style="display:block;margin-top:6px;font-size:0.85rem;color:var(--blue);font-weight:600;direction:rtl;">${ar}</span>`;
    translatedQ = true;
  } else {
    el.innerHTML = `<span>${q.q}</span>`;
    translatedQ = false;
  }
}

function translateOptions() {
  const opts = document.querySelectorAll('#opts-wrap .opt span');
  const q = currentQuestions[currentIndex];
  if (!translatedOpts) {
    opts.forEach((el, i) => {
      const ar = translateToArabic(q.opts[i]);
      el.innerHTML = `<span style="display:block;">${q.opts[i]}</span><span style="display:block;margin-top:4px;font-size:0.78rem;color:var(--blue);font-weight:600;direction:rtl;">${ar}</span>`;
    });
    translatedOpts = true;
  } else {
    opts.forEach((el, i) => { el.innerHTML = `<span>${q.opts[i]}</span>`; });
    translatedOpts = false;
  }
}

// ترجمة باستخدام Google Translate API المجاني
async function translateToArabic(text) {
  try {
    const url = `https://translate.googleapis.com/translate_a/single?client=gtx&sl=en&tl=ar&dt=t&q=${encodeURIComponent(text)}`;
    const res = await fetch(url);
    const data = await res.json();
    return data[0].map(x => x[0]).join('');
  } catch(e) {
    return '(تعذّرت الترجمة)';
  }
}

async function translateQuestion() {
  const el = document.getElementById('q-text');
  const q = currentQuestions[currentIndex];
  if (!translatedQ) {
    el.innerHTML = `<span>${q.q}</span><span style="display:block;margin-top:6px;font-size:0.82rem;color:var(--blue);font-weight:600;direction:rtl;">⏳ جاري الترجمة...</span>`;
    const ar = await translateToArabic(q.q);
    el.innerHTML = `<span style="display:block;">${q.q}</span><span style="display:block;margin-top:6px;font-size:0.85rem;color:var(--blue);font-weight:600;direction:rtl;">${ar}</span>`;
    translatedQ = true;
  } else {
    el.innerHTML = `<span>${q.q}</span>`;
    translatedQ = false;
  }
}

async function translateOptions() {
  const optsEls = document.querySelectorAll('#opts-wrap .opt span');
  const q = currentQuestions[currentIndex];
  if (!translatedOpts) {
    optsEls.forEach(el => {
      el.innerHTML = el.innerHTML + `<span style="display:block;margin-top:3px;font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--blue);">⏳</span>`;
    });
    const promises = q.opts.map(opt => translateToArabic(opt));
    const results = await Promise.all(promises);
    optsEls.forEach((el, i) => {
      el.innerHTML = `<span style="display:block;">${q.opts[i]}</span><span style="display:block;margin-top:4px;font-size:0.78rem;color:var(--blue);font-weight:600;direction:rtl;">${results[i]}</span>`;
    });
    translatedOpts = true;
  } else {
    optsEls.forEach((el, i) => { el.innerHTML = `<span>${q.opts[i]}</span>`; });
    translatedOpts = false;
  }
}

function toggleMode() {
  const body = document.body;
  const current = body.getAttribute('data-theme');
  body.setAttribute('data-theme', current === 'dark' ? 'light' : 'dark');
}

init();
</script>

</body>
</html>
